title: ULA Stacks Atlas V For Next National Security Launch
summary: United Launch Alliance (ULA) has stacked a Atlas V 551 rocket at SLC-41 on Cape Canaveral Space Force Station ahead of their next national security launch.

title: ULA delays NROL-107 launch, last Atlas NRO mission
summary: United Launch Alliance (ULA) has called off its Atlas V launch of the classified NROL-107 Silent Barker mission set for Tuesday. ULA noted that “out of an abundance of caution for personnel safety, a critical national security payload, and the approaching Tropical Storm Idalia,” the decision was made to return the rocket and payload to the vertical integration facility (VIF) at SLC-41.

title: ULA shooting for Sunday NROL-107 launch, last Atlas NRO mission
summary: United Launch Alliance (ULA) will try again Sunday to launch Atlas V with the classified NROL-107 Silent Barker mission set. The latest attempt comes after several days, including a rollback due to a hurricane threat.
